### Key Findings

- **Root cause**: `RAILWAY_TOKEN` expired/revoked — the `me{id}` GraphQL pre-flight check returned `Not Authorized`. No code bug; purely operational.
- **Token type matters**: The workflow uses `Authorization: Bearer` + `{me{id}}` query, which **requires an account-level token** per Railway docs. Do not use a project token — it will fail this validation.
- **Fix is documented**: `DEPLOYMENT_SECRETS.md` already has the exact rotation steps: create a new permanent account token at `railway.com/account/tokens`, then `gh secret set RAILWAY_TOKEN --repo alexsiri7/reli`, then rerun the failed CI job.
- **Recurrence pattern**: This is the 3rd+ token rotation in recent history (PRs #740, #741). When creating the replacement, confirm the Railway UI's "permanent" (no-expiry) option is selected — the prior tokens may have had a hidden TTL.

### Gaps

- Railway docs don't clarify whether "permanent" tokens truly never expire or have a maximum lifetime, which may explain the recurrence.

