**After**:
```python
def _validate_data_size(v: dict[str, Any] | None) -> dict[str, Any] | None:
def _validate_open_questions(v: list[str] | None) -> list[str] | None:
```
The same file uses unquoted form in all method signatures. Python 3.11 supports these natively; the quotes were holdovers with no purpose.

